%U A396318 22309287,26565,188955,1870,216315,838695,25935,3128,22724,174,812,6084351,7245,2090,60214
%N A396318 The terms of A091191 ordered by nonincreasing abundancy, where the abundancy of k is sigma(k)/k and sigma is the sum of divisors function, A000203. Terms with equal abundancy are in increasing order.
%C A396318 A091191 lists the larger of the 2 sets that bear the name "primitive abundant numbers" in OEIS, listing abundant numbers (A005101) that have no abundant proper divisor.
%C A396318 The equivalent sequence for A071395, the other set named "primitive abundant numbers", is A307098. The same principles apply here as outlined in the first comment in A307098 (which refers to a proof by Cohen).
